title: b'AJCAI  2022'
description: b'Australasian Joint Conference on Artificial Intelligence 2022'
Categories: b'AI' b'artificial intelligence' b'computer science' b'machine learning'
Call For Papers: b'\nThe 35th Australasian Joint Conference on Artificial Intelligence (AJCAI) will be held on 5-8 December 2022 in hybrid mode in Perth. AJCAI is the flagship conference for the Australasian AI community. It is also an annual event to advance communication between academic researchers and industry AI practitioners.\r We encourage cutting-edge work contributing to the theory and practice of AI. Novel application domains including cybersecurity, healthcare, IoT, robotics, social media and big data real-world applications are highly welcome.\r The conference topics are, but not limited to, the following.\r Topics\r - Agent-based, multiagent systems and game theory\r- Optimisation, constraint satisfaction, and search\r- Evolutionary computation and learning\r- Fuzzy and uncertainty of AI systems\r- Knowledge acquisition, ontologies, and representation\r- Planning, scheduling, combinatorial optimisation, and reinforcement learning\r- Cognitive modelling and computer-human interaction\r- Reasoning for AI systems and deep learning\r- Machine learning and deep learning related emerging topics\r- Multidisciplinary AI, and other emerging AI-related topics\r- AI applications and innovation, e.g., healthcare, education, entertainment, smart city, IoT, and blockchain\r- Computer vision and image processing\r- Natural language processing, text mining, and information retrieval\r- Data mining and knowledge discovery, web/social media mining, graph neural networks, and recommendation system\r- Robotics, human-robot Interaction, social robotics\r- Data-driven AI: big data, representation, analytics, and visualisation\r- AI infrastructure: cloud, networking, data warehouse, IoT, AutoML, and hardware\r- Ethical, legal, explainable, trustable, and accountable AI\r- Software engineering for AI, and AI project management\r- Privacy-preserving AI and federated learning\n\t'

title: b'EBGC 2022'
description: b'Exploring Boundaries of Global Citizenship'
Categories: b'education' b'21 century competancies' b'global citizenship' b'multidisciplinary'
Call For Papers: b'\nSwinburne Vietnam, a partnership between FPT University and Swinburne University of Technology, will hold the first international conference on global citizenship education and higher education, focussed on the role of universities in \xe2\x80\x9creadying\xe2\x80\x9d students to meet the challenges and demands of an ever changing world where they will need skills that go beyond subject specific knowledge and skills. The conference organising committee invites you to join us at Swinburne-Vietnam to explore the boundaries of global citizenship education and how global citizenship education may be redefined. \r The conference theme explores concepts of redefining how 21st Century competencies and global citizenship education (GCED) can prepare students for their role as active and engaged citizens, through practical and authentic real world educational opportunities. The recent pandemic has challenged currently held views about what is \xe2\x80\x9cnormal\xe2\x80\x9d and what a global citizen is, along with the knowledge, skills and values that are necessary for students to play a participatory role in today\xe2\x80\x99s society. \r How might transferable skills, 21st Century competencies, and global citizenship education prepare students for their role as active and engaged citizens, through practical and authentic real world educational opportunities.\r Sub-themes include, but are not limited to;\r    Creativity\r    Critical thinking and problem solving\r    Leadership\r    The role of digital technologies\r    Digital fluency\r    Beyond 21st century competencies\r    Intercultural understanding\r    Diversity and tolerance\r    Inclusiveness\r    Communication\r    Problem solving\r    Team work, coaching and mentoring\r    Resilience and adaptability\r    Questioning and reasoning\r    Applied learning\r    International diplomacy\r We look forward to receiving your abstract and seeing you at the conference. Attendance is limited, but free to attend for all accepted abstracts. \n\t'

title: b'DAIBC -  2022'
description: b'THE FIRST INTERNATIONAL WORKSHOP ON DECENTRALIZED AI USING BLOCKCHAIN '
Categories: b'blockchain' b'decentralized ai' b'computer science' b'machine learning'
Call For Papers: b'\nThe topics that are garnering much attention these times are Artificial intelligence and Blockchain. Blockchain is recently taking the shape of becoming a tool for security, validation and credibility purposes rather than just being used for mining cryptocurrency. Few of the primary use cases of blockchain outside of crypto currency are Health, Insurance, Supply chain management etc. On the other hand, Artificial Intelligence has been seen making steady progress into our lives with many topics like machine learning, facial recognition, navigation, search algorithms, social media, just to name a few. As the blockchain keeps a non-destroyable record of the transactions onto the decentralized network, artificial intelligence could be developed to learn the transactions in the blockchain and detect the consequences in the future, rather than use/create artificial intelligence on centralized servers with the help of machine learning. To summarize, the intention of the workshop will be to prove that a Blockchain-based decentralized decision making and learning processes are expected to improve the accuracy and efficacy of the results than the ones based on conventional centralized decision making and learning processes.\r The workshop welcomes original research, related idea, and innovative solutions and focus on either fundamental methodological studies or use cases and application demonstrations. Authors are invited to submit original research contributions that fall into or are related topic areas listed below:\r Blockchain-enabled artificial intelligence frameworks\rAI and blockchain in Health industry\rDecentralized AI\rGreen blockchain using AI\rMachine learning using Blockchain\rBlockchain enabled robotics\rDecentralized Machine learning\rBlockchain based AI tools and simulations\rInfrastructures built with AI on blockchain\rDeep Learning using Blockchain\n\t'

title: b'RSICCI 2023'
description: b'CFP for Regional Special Issue: Climate Change in Italy'
Call For Papers: b'\nDear Colleagues,\r As a region that is more sensitive to climate change, the Mediterranean is warming faster than the global average. The Italian peninsula, together with the whole Central Mediterranean area, have been impacted significantly over the last few decades. Extreme weather events have caused serious damage, while climate processes have impacted health and ecosystems, creating new risks determined not only by weather events but also by changing exposures and vulnerabilities. Several coastal zones face disasters, including flooding and erosion, and the salinization of river deltas and aquifers that sustain food security and livelihoods. Indeed, the Italian mountains continue to become warmer and drier. Again, for the Central Mediterranean, several models foresee further warming, droughts, and long-lasting modifications. What will the physical geographical consequences be based on current trends and forecasting?\r This Special Issue aims to invite scholars to submit research on the physical impacts of climate change on the Italian peninsula as well as the whole Central Mediterranean area. It intends to promote a discussion on climate change\xe2\x80\x99s impact on coastal and mountain zones and the related challenges from the perspective of physical geography. We are looking for research on: the analysis of extreme events; the forecasting and application of observation and forecasting methods; empirical studies; case studies; and modeling and projection studies for the near and far future.\r Dr. Delle Rose Marco\rDr. Maria Teresa Caccamo\rGuest Editors\n\t'

title: b'CCACF 2022'
description: b'CFP for Special Issue Climate Change Adaptation Costs and Finance'
Call For Papers: b'\nDear Colleagues,\r Climate change and the associated increase in the frequency and magnitude of extreme events constitute the hardest and longest-standing challenge to human wellbeing faced by societies across the globe. Adapting to climate change means mitigating natural hazards through multiple material and intangible investments, which bear a significant cost and require dealing with unique uncertainties. Scientific knowledge about the costs of adaptation and about the financing of actions to support adaptation is today extremely limited at any scale, significantly reducing our capability to support stakeholders making these crucial decisions. This Special Issue thus aims at supporting climate policies by outlining the scientific state of the art on adaptation costs and adaptation funding mechanisms.\r In this Special Issue, original research articles and reviews are welcome. Research areas may include (but are not limited to) the following:\r     Assessments of adaptation costs in specific industries;\r    Case studies of adaptation actions, costs, and funding strategies in local communities;\r    Cost function analyses of adaptation actions;\r    Cost of nature-based investments in adaptation;\r    Ecosystem services appropriation for adaptation;\r    Urban vs. rural adaptation costs;\r    Evaluations of UN adaptation fund tools and results;\r    Cost/benefit analyses of climate finance tools;\r    Bottlenecks and credit crunching for adaptation;\r    Financial costs of adaptation;\r    Market failures and missing markets in climate finance;\r    Public vs. private funding mechanisms for adaptation;\r    Mechanism design in climate finance;\r    Systems science and complexity science approaches to adaptation;\r    Methodologies and reviews for all of the above.\r I look forward to receiving your contributions.\r Dr. Riccardo Boero\rGuest Editor\n\t'

title: b'RCCIA 2023'
description: b'CFP for Special Issue Recent Climate Change Impacts in Australia'
Call For Papers: b'\nDear Colleagues,\r The main threats of climate change in Australia, as elsewhere, resulting from the increase in temperature of the Earth\xe2\x80\x99s atmosphere and oceans, include ecosystem collapse, more frequent severe weather, longer and more frequent droughts, and rising sea levels. The increasing temperatures at the poles are amplified by warmer oceans causing ice melt and rising sea levels, leading to lower oxygen in ocean habitats and killing coral reefs. The extreme coral bleaching event of 2016 resulted in a loss of approximately one-third of shallow-water coral cover in Australia\xe2\x80\x99s Great Barrier Reef. The combination of warming atmosphere and oceans is altering rainfall patterns, affecting the sustainability of a wide range of ecosystems. Dry rivers and streams in southeast Australia during a recent drought resulted in mass fish deaths in southeast Australia, and further fish deaths occurred in recent river surges from flooding rains that mixed with toxic water caused by algal blooms.\r In summary, global warming is already leading to dramatic changes in the Australian climate, with impacts on ecosystems and most aspects of human health, economic activity and wellbeing.\r This Special Issue welcomes all studies related to climate change impacts in Australia.\r Dr. Milton S. Speer\rProf. Dr. Lance Leslie\rGuest Editors\n\t'

title: b'ACMIP6MEP 2023'
description: b'CFP for Special Issue Application of CMIP6 Models in Extreme Precipitation'
Call For Papers: b'\nDear Colleagues,\r Recently, evaluation of the potential future vulnerability and impact of climate change on water resources have been widely studied on the regional and global scale using the most recent CMIP6 climate data simulations. Studies on climate change impacts on extreme climate such as flood and drought are able to adapt and reduce their potential damages. The Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC) recently released a new climate simulation from The Coupled Model Intercomparison Project Phase 6 (CMIP6), which is an updated version of the general circulation model (GCM). This new CMIP6 GCM is expected to be an improvement of the projection of future climate. The CMIP6 has designed new scenarios called shared socioeconomic pathways (SSP) to include socioeconomic factors such as the growth of population, economics, urbanization, and other factors into climate simulation. This Special Issue aims to collect original studies and reviews as outcomes from CMIP6 climate datasets on water resources and extreme climate.\r Dr. Oeurng Chantha\rDr. Try Sophal\rDr. Sok Ty\rGuest Editors\n\t'

title: b'DALS 2022'
description: b'Data Science for Life Science'
Categories: b'data science' b'bioinformatics' b'life science' b'data analysis'
Call For Papers: b'\nDear All,\r We invite submissions to the 1st International Workshop on Data Analysis in Life Science in conjunction with ECML PKDD 2022. It will be focus on improving data-driven personalized medicine, genetic data management, and health care system advancement. It will involve data management and analysis, machine learning, and knowledge discovery applied to bioinformatics, healthcare, and life science problems.\r The topics of interest include, but are not limited to:\r - Visualization and exploratory analysis methods for genomic and health care data\r- Data analysis of genomics and molecular biology data\r- Knowledge discovery from biological and clinical databases\r- Analysis of electronic health records (EHR)\r- Data analysis of heterogeneous health information systems and databases\r- Natural language processing methods applied to genomics and healthcare data\r- Tracking and visualization of the viral sequences\r- Machine learning methods applied to viral sequences\r- Deep learning methods for bioinformatics and biomedical images\r- Data pre-processing approaches for single-cell data\r- Single-cell data analysis\r- Data integration practices for precision medicine\r- Network-based approaches for genomic data analysis\r We invite contributions from both industry and academia to share their research and experience in using data science, machine learning and database knowledge practices with biological and clinical data.\r Submitted papers will be evaluated based on their novelty, technical quality, and potential impact. Experimental methods and results are expected to be reproducible, and authors are strongly encouraged to make code and data available. Work in progress is welcome, but preliminary results should be made available as a proof of concept. Submissions only consisting of a proposal will be rejected. \r Key Dates\rThe following deadlines are in AoE time zone (UTC \xe2\x80\x93 12).\r Paper submission: 20 June 2022\rNotification: 13 July 2022\rECML PKDD Conference dates: September 19-23, 2022\rWorkshop DALS date: September 19 (Online)\r More information can be found here: http://www.bioinformatics.deib.polimi.it/DALS2022/\r Regards,\rArif Canakoglu, Gaia Ceddia, Sara Pid\xc3\xb2, Pietro Pinoli\n\t'

13th International Conference on Ubiquitous Computing (UBIC 2022)

November 26 ~ 27, 2022, London, United Kingdom

Scope & Topics

13th International Conference on Ubiquitous Computing (UBIC 2022)will provide an excellent international forum for sharing knowledge and results in theory, methodology and applications of Ubiquitous Computing. Current information age is witnessing a dramatic use of digital and electronic devices in the workplace and beyond. Ubiquitous Computing presents a rather arduous requirement of robustness, reliability and availability to the end user. Ubiquitous computing has received a significant and sustained research interest in terms of designing and deploying large scale and high performance computational applications in real life. The aim of the conference is to provide a platform to the researchers and practitioners from both academia as well as industry to meet and share cutting-edge development in the field.

Authors are solicited to contribute to the conference by submitting articles that illustrate research results, projects, surveying works and industrial experiences that describe significant advances in the following areas, but are not limited to.

Topics of interest include, but are not limited to, the following

  • Architectural Structure, Design Decisions and Philosophies\r
  • Autonomic Management of Ubiquitous Systems\r
  • Context and Location Awareness, Context
  • Based and Implicit Computing\r
  • Distributed Computing\r
  • Ubicomp Human-Computer Interaction for Devices\r
  • Intelligent Devices and Environments\r
  • Internet Computing and Applications\r
  • Interoperability and Large Scale Deployment\r
  • Middleware Services and Agent Technologies\r
  • Dependable, Reliable and Autonomic Computing\r
  • Personalized & Special Field Applications\r
  • Security Issues and Applications\r
  • Service Discovery Mechanisms and Protocols\r
  • Software Infrastructures\r
  • System Support Infrastructures and Services\r
  • Ubiquitous Systems and Trust\r
  • User Interfaces and Interaction Models\r
  • Virtualization Over Networks of Devices\r
  • Wearable Computers and Technologies\r
  • Wireless Networking and Mobile, Pervasive and Ubiquitous Computing\r
  • Wireless/Mobile Service Management and Delivery\r
  • Mobile Computing\r
  • Network Protocols & Wireless Communication

Paper Submission

Authors are invited to submit papers through the conference Submission System by August 27, 2022. Submissions must be original and should not have been published previously or be under consideration for publication while being evaluated for this conference. The proceedings of the conference will be published by Computer Science Conference Proceedings in Computer Science & Information Technology (CS & IT) series (Confirmed).

Selected papers from UBIC 2022, after further revisions, will be published in the special issues of the following journals.

  • International Journal of Computer Networks & Communications (IJCNC)-Scopus, WJCI, ERA Indexed
  • International Journal of UbiComp (IJU)
  • International Journal of Ad hoc, Sensor & Ubiquitous Computing (IJASUC)
  • Information Technology in Industry (ITII)

Important Dates

Submission Deadline: August 27, 2022
Authors Notification: September 25, 2022
Final Manuscript Due: October 04, 2022

title: b'Metaverse 2022'

Categories: b'metaverse architectures and re' b'business scenarios in metavers' b'service components in metavers' b'data and intelligence in metav'
Call For Papers: b"\nInternational Conference on Metaverse (METAVERSE 2022) Call for Papers\rThe Services Sector has account for 79.5% of the GDP of United States in 2016. For the world's most services-oriented economy, its  services sectors account for more than 90% of GDP. Currently, most of the services are traditional services (e.g. restaurant, travel, transportation, etc.) and digital services (e.g. Internet services, mobile services, digital transformation enabled services, etc.). With the emergence of Metaverse, the current services will be gradually transformed into immersive services that construct digital worlds and connect with physical worlds. The immersive services are the core characteristics of metaverse. \r To rapidly respond to the changing economy, the 2022 World Congress on Services (SERVICES 2022) has been naturally extended to become the International Conference on Metaverse (METAVERSE 2022) to cover immersive services for all vertical industries and area solutions. puts its focus on the industry-specific services for digital transformation. Part of the SCF 2018, SERVICES 2018 was successfully held on June 25 - June 30, 2018, Seattle, USA. Part of the SCF 2019, SERVICES 2019 was successfully held on June 25 - 30, 2019, San Diego, USA. Part of the SCF 2020, SERVICES 2020 and SERVICES 2021 was successfully held over the Internet. In 2022, we will celebrate our 2022 version of gathering, to strive to advance the largest international professional forum on industry services research and practices.\r METAVERSE 2022 is a member of Services Conference Federation (SCF). SCF 2022 will have the following 10 collocated service-oriented sister conferences: 2022 International Conference on Web Services (ICWS 2022), 2022 International Conference on Cloud Computing (CLOUD 2022), 2022 International Conference on Services Computing (SCC 2022), 2022 International Conference on Big Data (BigData 2022), 2022 International Conference on AI & Mobile Services (AIMS 2022), and 2022 International Conference on Metaverse (METAVERSE 2022), 2022 International Conference on Internet of Things (ICIOT 2022), 2022 International conference on Cognitive Computing (ICCC 2022), 2022 International Conference on Edge Computing (EDGE 2022), and 2022 International Conference on Blockchain (ICBC 2022). \r  As the founding member of the Services Conference Federation (SCF), the first International Conference on Web Services (ICWS) was held in June 2003 in Las Vegas, USA. Meanwhile, the First International Conference on Web Services - Europe 2003 (ICWS-Europe 2003) was held in Germany in October 2003. ICWS-Europe'03 is an extended event of the 2003 International Conference on Web Services (ICWS 2003) in Europe. In 2004, ICWS-Europe was changed to the European Conference on Web Services (ECOWS), which was held at Erfurt, Germany. \r Sponsored by Services Society and Springer, SCF 2018 and SCF 2019 were held successfully in Seattle and San Diego, USA. SCF 2020 and SCF 2021 was held successfully online and in Shenzhen, China. To celebrate its 20-year-old birthday, SCF 2022 will be held on December 10 - 14, 2022.\r Conference Proceedings\rThe Proceedings of METAVERSE 2022 will be published in the Lecture Notes in Computer Science (LNCS) by Springer International Publishing AG. Currently the Abstracting and Indexing services covered by Springer\xe2\x80\x99s data feeds for LNCS proceedings include ISI Conference Proceedings Citation Index (included in Web of Science), Engineering Index EI (Compendex and Inspec databases), DBLP, Google Scholar, IO-Port, MathSciNet, Scopus, and ZBlMath. The Best Paper Awards will be sponsored by Springer, which is a leading global scientific, technical and medical portfolio, providing researchers in academia, scientific institutions and corporate R&D departments with quality content through innovative information, products and services.\r Extended versions of selected papers will be invited for special issues in the Services Transactions on Internet of Things (STIOT), Services Transactions on Big Data (STBD), Services Transactions on Services Computing (STSC), Services Transactions on Cloud Computing (STCC), International Journal of Web Services Research (JWSR), and International Journal of Business Process Integration and Management (IJBPIM). JWSR is indexed by SCI and EI [Link].\r Topics\rMETAVERSE 2022 organizing committee invites you to participate in 2022 edition of METAVERSE, to be held on December 10 - 14, 2022. \r The technical program of METAVERSE 2022 will include a Research Track, an Application Track, and a Short Paper Track. The METAVERSE 2022 tracks seeks original, UNPUBLISHED research papers reporting substantive new work in various aspects of vertical industry services and related technologies and applications. Research Track papers MUST clearly indicate their contributions to the field of vertical services industry in terms of technologies, applications and solutions. All papers MUST properly cite related work in the field, such as those published in the proceedings of ICWS, SCC, CLOUD, AIMS, METAVERSE, BigData, ICIOT, ICBC, EDGE, APSCC, ECOWS, and related journals including STBD, JWSR, STSC, STCC, STIOT and IJBPIM (see Literature Recommendations page).\r METAVERSE 2022 hopes to attract researchers, practitioners, and industry business leaders in all the following services sectors to help define and shape the modernization strategy and directions of the services industry. You are invited to submit research, engineering, experience reports, case studies, empirical, evaluation and business innovation papers on the following topics. \r Metaverse Architectures and Realizations\r - User Interactions in Metaverse\r- Business Scenarios in Metaverse\r- Services Store in Metaverse\r- Service Components in Metaverse\r- Infrastructure in Metaverse\r- Integration in Metaverse\r- Data and Intelligence in Metaverse\r- Security and Privacy in Metaverse\r- Quality of Services in Metaverse\r- Governance in Metaverse\r Metaverse Applications for Vertical Services Industry and Domain Solutions\r- Advertising Services\r- Banking Services\r- Broadcasting & Cable TV Services\r- Business Services\r- Casinos & Gaming Services\r- Communications Services\r- Cross-industry Services (e.g. strategy and planning, supply chain management, enterprise resource planning, customer relationship management, marketing services)\r- Design Automation Services\r- Energy and Utilities Services\r- Financial Services\r- Government Services\r- Healthcare Services\r- Hotels & Motels Services\r- Insurance Services\r- Internet Services\r- Motion Pictures Services\r- Personal Services\r- Printing & Publishing Services\r- Real Estate Operations Services\r- Recreational Activities Services\r- Rental & Leasing Services\r- Restaurants Services\r- Retail Services (Apparel, Catalog & Mail Order, Department & Discount, Drugs, Grocery, Home Improvement, Specialty, Technology)\r- Schools and Education Services\r- Security Systems & Services\r- Technology Services\r- Travel and Transportation Services\r- Waste Management Services\r- Wholesale Distribution Services\r- Human Resource Services\r- Supply Chain Services\r- Enterprise Architecture Services\r- the Industry on Services Privacy\r Papers that relate to metaverse architectural building blocks and applications are particularly encouraged.\r Paper Submissions\rAll submitted manuscripts will be peer-reviewed by at least 3 program committee members. Accepted and presented papers from all METAVERSE tracks will appear in the conference proceedings.  Submitted Research Track and Application Track manuscripts will be limited to 15 (LNCS Proceedings style) pages and REQUIRED to be formatted using the LNCS Proceedings template ( WORD , Latex ). Submitted Short Paper track manuscripts will be limited to 8 (LNCS Proceedings style) pages. The authors can extend a maximum of 2 pages for each paper but will have to pay extra fees for each extra page. Unformatted papers and papers beyond the maximum page limit may not be reviewed. Electronic submission of manuscripts (in PDF or Word format) is required. Detailed instructions for electronic paper preparation and submission, panel proposals, tutorial proposals, workshop proposals, and review process can be found at conference site.\r The Proceedings of METAVERSE 2022 will be published in the Lecture Notes in Computer Science (LNCS) by Springer International Publishing AG. For all 10 collocated conferences of SCF 2022, the content of this proceedings volume will be made freely accessible to anyone in the Springer\xe2\x80\x99s digital library after four years upon publication.\r At least one author of each accepted paper is required to register to the conference and present the paper. One Best Paper award and one Best Student Paper award will be granted at METAVERSE 2022. The Best Paper Awards will be sponsored by Services Society and Springer, which is a leading global scientific, technical and medical portfolio, providing researchers in academia, scientific institutions and corporate R&D departments with quality content through innovative information, products and services. The first author of the best student paper must be a full-time student.\r Manuscripts submitted to the Research Track focusing on applications or solutions  may be recommended to the Application Track or other tracks for further consideration if the session slots are available. \r METAVERSE 2022 Submission\r METAVERSE 2022 Research Track:\rhttps://www.edas.info/newPaper.php?c=29827&track=112973\r METAVERSE 2022 Application and Industry Track:\rhttps://www.edas.info/newPaper.php?c=29827&track=112972\r METAVERSE 2022 Short Paper Track:\rhttps://www.edas.info/newPaper.php?c=29827&track=112974\r For other co-located conferences, you can find detailed submission instructions and links from the Submission page.\r Important Dates\rResearch Track/Application Track/Short Paper Track/Special Track:\rEarly-birds paper submission due: June 26, 2022\r Review comments to Early-birds paper submission: July 20, 2022\r Regular paper submission due: August 15, 2022\r Review comments to Regular paper submission: September 13, 2022\r Camera ready manuscripts due: September 20, 2022\r Conference dates: December 10 - 14, 2022\n\t"

title: b'ITQM-SCODM 2022'
description: b'ITQM - Soft Computing and Optimization for Decision-Making'
Categories: b'soft computing' b'fuzzy logic' b'multi-criteria decision making' b'multi-objective optimization'
Call For Papers: b'\nThe Ninth International Conference on Information Technology and Quantitative Management (ITQM 2022) is one of the conference series organized by International Academy of Information Technology and Quantitative Management (IAITQM)\r ----------\rSpecial Session 06: Soft Computing and Optimization for Decision-Making\r Session Chairs:\r- Prof. Bogdana Stanojevi\xc4\x87, Mathematical Institute of the Serbian Academy of Sciences and Arts, Serbia,  bgdnpop@mi.sanu.ac.rs\r- Prof. Boris Deliba\xc5\xa1i\xc4\x87, University of Belgrade, Serbia,  boris.delibasic@fon.bg.ac.rs\r ----------\rWe cordially invite papers addressing new methods and applications in the areas of soft computing and optimization methods. Despite the prevalent use of fully automated machine learning methods, expert-based methods and their combination with machine learning methods still play an important role in decision-making as they try to bind two worlds in decision-making, the expert based and the data based.\r With soft computing methods and tools one can exploit domain knowledge about the problem at hand, model uncertainty, and imprecision in measurements robustly and with low computation cost. By doing this one enhances the context of the decision-making process and offers comprehensiveness (greater interpretability and explainability) of the decision being made.\r This session aims to present state-of-the-art research on soft computing and optimization, and its application to either expert- or algorithmic-based decision making. Having this in mind, we solicit submissions in all aspects of soft computing and optimization for decision-making, from mathematical foundations of soft computing and optimization for decision-making, novel approaches and methods, and its applications for business purposes or for proposing solutions for social problems.\r ----------\rTopics of interest in this session are presented in the following non-exhaustive list:\r- Soft computing;\r- Fuzzy logic, fuzzy sets and systems and their extensions;\r- Fuzzy decision-making and decision support systems;\r- Fuzzy optimization;\r- Optimization methods and applications for decision-making;\r- Multi-criteria decision-making;\r- Soft computing and optimization in data mining and machine learning;\r- Soft computing and optimization for social good;\r- Multi-objective optimization;\r- Mathematical theory for modeling uncertainty;\r- Decision making under uncertainty;\r- Approximate reasoning, and others.\n\t'

title: b'UCAmI 2022'
description: b'14th International Conference on Ubiquitous Computing and Ambient Intelligence'
Categories: b'ambient intelligence' b'ubiquitous computing' b'healthcare' b'human-computer interaction'
Call For Papers: b'\nThe Ubiquitous Computing (UC) idea envisioned by Weiser in 1991, has recently evolved to a more general paradigm known as Ambient Intelligence (AmI) that represents a new generation of user-centred computing environments and systems. These solutions aim to find new ways to obtain a better integration of information technology in everyday life devices and activities.\rAmI environments are integrated by several autonomous computational devices of modern life ranging from consumer electronics to mobile phones. Ideally, people in an AmI environment will not notice these devices, but they will benefit from the services these solutions provide them. Such devices are aware of the people present in those environments by reacting to their gestures, actions and context. Recently the interest in AmI environments has grown considerably due to new challenges posed by society, demanding highly innovative services, such as vehicular ad hoc networks (VANET), Ambient Assisted Living (AAL), e-Health, Internet of Things and Home Automation among others. The main focus of this edition of the UCAmI Conference will be "Ambient Intelligence: Sensing, Processing and Using Environmental Information".\r All accepted papers will be included in Proceedings published by Springer. Selected papers will be published in the following journals:\r- Journal of Wireless Networks (IF(2020) = 2.602)\r- Journal of Personal and Ubiquitous Computing (IF(2020) = 3.006)\r(More journals to be announced shortly on https://ucami.org)\n\t'

title: b'PRDC 2022'
description: b'The 27th IEEE Pacific Rim International Symposium on Dependable Computing '
Call For Papers: b"\nIEEE PRDC 2022 is the twenty-seventh event in a series of symposia started in 1989 devoted to dependable and fault-tolerant computing. PRDC is recognized as the main event in the Pacific area that covers many dimensions of dependability and fault tolerance, encompassing fundamental theoretical approaches, practical experimental projects, and commercial components and systems. As applications of computing systems have permeated into all aspects of daily life, the dependability of computing systems has become increasingly critical. This symposium provides a forum for countries around the Pacific Rim and other areas of the world to exchange ideas for improving the dependability of computing systems.\rTopics of interest include (but are not limited to):\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Software and hardware reliability, resilience, safety, security, testing,\rverification, and validation\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Dependability measurement, modeling, evaluation, and tools\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Self-healing, self-protecting, and fault-tolerant systems\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Architecture and system design for dependability\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Prognostics in Complex Systems\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Reliability analysis of Complex Systems\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Fault-tolerant algorithms and protocols\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Cloud computing resiliency, security and privacy\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Software defined networks architectures and protocols\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Dependability issues in computing systems (e.g. computer networks and\rcommunications, high performance computing, real-time systems, storage and databases systems, cyber-physical systems, socio-technical systems, and blockchain and smart contracts).\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Emerging technologies (autonomous systems including autonomous vehicles, human machine teaming, smart devices/Internet of Things)\rSubmission and Publication Information\rManuscripts may be submitted in IEEE double-column format to one of the following two categories: (i) Regular Papers and (ii) Practical Experience Reports.\rRegular Papers (10 pages, excluding references and appendices) should describe original research (not submitted or published elsewhere).\rPractical Experience Reports (6 pages, excluding references and appendices) should describe an experience or a case study, such as the design and deployment of a system or actual failure and recovery field data.\rAll submissions must be made electronically (in PDF format) through the submission website. Please note that all submissions will undergo a double-blind review. Please ensure that you have removed any references that could lead to the disclosure of the authors' identities. Failing to do so may result in rejection of the paper regardless of the paper contributions. Papers will be reviewed by program committee members from the international community and selected based on their originality, significance, relevance, and clarity of presentation. All accepted papers will be published by the IEEE Computer Society Press (EI Indexed). Submission of a contribution to the track indicates agreement to have one author present the work, if accepted, at the conference. In light of the ongoing COVID-19 pandemic, virtual presentation and attendance options will be available to accommodate all participants.\rOne outstanding paper will be selected to receive the Best Paper Award, and one outstanding paper first-authored by a student will receive the Best Student Paper Award. A few excellent papers will be recommended to have their extended versions submitted to IEEE Transactions on Dependable and Secure Computing (TDSC) or a Special Issue of the Software Testing, Verification and Reliability (STVR) journal.\n\t"

Categories: b'digital learning' b'information science' b'digital humanities' b'techno-cultural data'
Call For Papers: b'\nPNC 2022 Annual Conference and Joint Meetings\rCall for Papers & Posters (Extended to June 15)\r Main Theme: The Digital World in an Age of Uncertainty: Humanizing Technology for Wellness, Resilience, and Creativity\rDate: September 16th-18th (Friday-Sunday)\rVenue: The University of Arizona, Tucson, USA\rURL: https://sites.google.com/view/pnc-2022/conference-info  \r________________________________________\rDear Colleagues,\r Due to many requests, the deadline of Call for Papers and Posters has been extended to June 15, 2022 (UTC+08:00).\r It is our great pleasure to announce that the PNC 2022 Annual Conference and Joint Meetings (PNC 2022) will take place in the University of Arizona (Tucson), USA from September 16th-18th, 2022. The main theme of the PNC 2022 is \xe2\x80\x9cThe Digital World in an Age of Uncertainty: Humanizing Technology for Wellness, Resilience, and Creativity\xe2\x80\x9d.\r The PNC 2022 serves as an opportunity for researchers and developers to facilitate information exchanges among institutions of higher education in the Pacific Rim through computing and communications technology. PNC explores issues of information and technology exchange, interdisciplinary collaboration, and the development of the cultural knowledge contents. The technical program of PNC 2022 will include invited keynotes, paper presentations, workshops and poster session. We welcome submissions that focus on but not limited to the following topics:\r 1. Digital Learning \r1.1 Learning and Teaching Technology \r1.2 Digitized Area Studies \r1.3 Digital Heritage \r1.4 Language Teaching and Learning \r 2. Information Science and E-business \r2.1 Library, Archival, and Museum Studies \r2.2 Machine Translation and Deep Learning \r2.3 Digital Media \r2.4 E-health and Wellness Studies \r2.5 Biodiversity\r2.6 Artificial Intelligence \r2.7 Digital Archives \r 3. Digital Humanities \r3.1 Archaeology \r3.2 Digital Libraries\r3.3 Digital Museums \r3.4 Digital Sinology\r3.5 History, Literature, and Philosophy \r3.6 Virtual Reality, Augmented Reality, and the Metaverse\r3.7 Spatial Analysis and GIS \r3.8 Holographic/Volumetric Video Broadcast/Capture \r 4. Techno-cultural Data in a Post-pandemic World\r4.1 Machine Intelligence\r4.2 Digitaltwins\r4.3 Mirrorworlds\r4.4 Cryptocurrency\r4.5 Cultural Memory\r4.6 Blockchain Codes of Ownership\r4.7 Archival Artefacts\r4.8 Imaging Technics\r4.9 Digital Replicas\r4.10 Interfaces: Mixed, Augmented, and Virtual\r4.11 Interactive Immersion\r Submission Categories\rFor Presentation: Abstract Submission (1 page) / Full Paper Submission (6-8 pages)\rFor Poster & Demo: Abstract Submission (no more than 500 words)\r*Abstract submission (1 page) and acceptance are required to deliver a presentation at the Conference. Full Paper submission (6-8 pages) is optional, but required if authors want their papers considered for the IEEE Xplore Conference Proceedings.\r Guidelines for Abstract/Paper Submission \rhttps://sites.google.com/view/pnc-2022/call-for-papers-and-posters/abstractpaper-submission\r Authors are invited to submit the abstracts or full papers through the online submission system by June 15, 2022 (UTC+08:00). The final manuscript (camera ready) should be ready by July 31, 2022 (UTC+08:00). \r Kindly note that there will be NO hybrid sessions in this event.  Most sessions are going to be in-person in Tucson with no live streaming. Few online-only sessions would be prepared due to the ongoing development of the COVID-19.\r Submissions must be original and should not have been published previously while being evaluated for this conference. The full paper length is 6-8 pages, including figures and tables but not including references. All submitted papers must conform to the IEEE Xplore Format for conference proceedings.\r As the reviewing will be blind, papers must not include authors\' names and affiliations. Furthermore, self-references that reveal the author\'s identity, e.g., "We previously showed (Smith, 1991) ..." must be avoided. Instead, use citations such as "Smith previously showed (Smith, 1991) ..." Papers that do not conform to these requirements will be rejected without review.\r Papers should not refer, for further detail, to documents that are not available to the reviewers. For example, do not omit or redact important citation information to preserve anonymity. Instead, use third person or named reference to this work, as described above (\xe2\x80\x9cSmith showed\xe2\x80\x9d rather than \xe2\x80\x9cwe showed\xe2\x80\x9d).\r Guidelines for Poster Submission\rhttps://sites.google.com/view/pnc-2022/call-for-papers-and-posters/poster-submission \r Authors are invited to submit the abstracts (no more than 500 words) through the online submission system by June 15, 2022 (UTC+08:00). The final manuscript (camera ready) should be ready by July 31, 2022 (UTC+08:00).  There are two categories of PNC 2022 Poster Session: Poster Competition and Demonstration Zone.\r I. Poster Competition\rFor the poster competition, the participants are required to give an oral orientation in-person in Tucson. The best poster award will be selected after evaluation by the Grading Committee. Below please find detailed selection criteria and grading standards.\r II. Demonstration Zone\rFor poster demonstration only. Vendors or Institutions are welcome to take this opportunity to show research results that are related to the conference main theme.\r Important Dates:\rSubmission Deadline: May 31, 2022    June 15, 2022 (UTC+08:00)\rNotification of Acceptance: June 30, 2022   July 10, 2022 (UTC+08:00)\rFinal Submission (Camera Ready): July 31, 2022\rConference Date: September 16-18, 2022\r Hosts\rThe College of Humanities, University of Arizona, USA\rPacific Neighborhood Consortium (PNC)\r Co-hosts\rAcademia Sinica\rElectronic Cultural Atlas Initiative (ECAI)\rMinistry of Education, Taiwan\r Local Organizers\rCenter for Buddhist Studies, University of Arizona, USA\rDepartment of East Asian Studies, University of Arizona, USA\r Co-sponsors\rSchool of Information, University of Arizona, USA\rCenter for Digital Society and Data Studies, University of Arizona, USA\rCenter for Digital Humanities, University of Arizona, USA\r Technical Sponsor\rIEEE Tucson Section AP/MTT/COM/EMC Joint Chapter\rInstitute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE)\r  About Pacific Neighborhood Consortium (PNC) \rSince 1993, the PNC has been committed to enhancing digital research and interaction among researchers, educators, and professionals around the Pacific Rim nations. The importance and contribution of the PNC has been widely recognized by the digital and information technology community. To learn more about the PNC, please visit the website at https://www.pnclink.org/\r  PNC Secretariat\rP.O. Box 76 Academia Sinica, Taipei 11599, Taiwan\rTel: +886-2-2652-1885# 307or309\rEmail: pnc@gate.sinica.edu.tw\rWebsite: https://www.pnclink.org\r\n'

Call For Papers: b"\n5th International Congress on Economics, Finance & Energy (EFE'2022) titled \xe2\x80\x9cMonetary and Fiscal Policies in Post-Pandemic World: Lessons, Issues and Challenges\xe2\x80\x9d  will be held in a hybrid format with both in-person and online attendance on September 7-9, 2022.\r Dear Colleague,\rWe are pleased to announce that the 5th International Congress on Economics, Finance & Energy (EFE\xe2\x80\x992022) titled \xe2\x80\x98Monetary and Fiscal Policies in Post-Pandemic World: Lessons, Issues and Challenges\xe2\x80\x99 which will be held in Turkistan, Kazakhstan and provides a hybrid format with both in-person and online attendance on September 7-9, 2022.\r This Congress will be jointly organized by Khoja Akhmet Yassawi International Kazakh-Turkish University, International University of Sarajevo and University of New York Tirana. In EFE\xe2\x80\x992022 we invite you to gather in Turkistan in-person and online to discuss the economic conditions in the post-pandemic world which severely affect every single countries\xe2\x80\x99 economy.\r In detail, our talks and discussion would include monetary and fiscal policies, the situation in financial markets, ongoing uncertainties and risks which occur due to prolonging the pandemic and its restrictive measures. Moreover, we would welcome a different range of topics like rapid development of cryptocurrencies usage areas and metaverse. EFE\xe2\x80\x992022 aims to establish a platform for scholars and experts to share their experiences and ideas on how economies are managing their policies in a post-pandemic world.\r The participants are expected to submit the abstracts of their papers (200-250 words), which include the problem statement, explanation of the hypotheses, methods used and the research results, to the Congress Submission System no later than 1 July 2022. The Congress will be held in English, Turkish, Kazakh, Russian and other Turkic languages. The papers and abstracts can be submitted in one of these languages.\r If you have any questions, please email to\rinfo@efecongress.org.\rhttp://www.efecongress.org\r Important Dates\rDeadline for Abstract Submission: 15 June 2022\rNotification of Acceptance: 15 July 2022\rDeadline for Registration Fee Payment: 30 July 2022\rCongress Program Announcement : 15 August 2022\rCongress Dates: 7-9 September 2022\rDeadline for Full Paper Submission: 30 September 2022\r The topics of the Congress:\rFiscal Policies\rMonetary Policies\rCentral Banking\rFinancial Markets, Institutions, and Integration\rCryptocurrencies\rMetaverse\rUncertainty and Risk\rPolitical Instability\rGlobal Value Chains\rSustainable Development\rGrowth and Distribution\rThe Changing Nature of Work and Employment\rOther Topics in Economics, Finance and Energy\r Publication\rPrior to Congress, Abstracts book will be published. As for the Book of Proceedings, all accepted full papers will be published in the proceedings book (with an ISBN number). Also, Congress participants will have the opportunity to publish their papers in English in the Eurasian Research Journal or in an edited book. The papers can be sent to be reviewed as a book chapter. Congress participants need to send their final version of their papers until 30 September 2022.\r\n"

details about submission, please via: http://www.isai.org/sub.html\r \xe2\x98\x85Conference Schedule\xe2\x98\x85\rDay 1, 26 April, 2023 10:00 \xe2\x80\x93 15:00 Registration, collecting conference Presentation\r \xe2\x98\x85Chengdu, China\xe2\x98\x85\rChengdu, the capital of China's southwest Sichuan Province, is famed for being the home of cute giant pandas. Located in the west of Sichuan Basin and in the center of Chengdu Plain, the city covers a total area of 12.3 thousand square kilometres (4,749 square miles) with a population of over 11 million.\rBenefiting from Dujiangyan Irrigation Project which was constructed in 256 B.C., Sichuan Province is reputed as the Heavenly State, Tian Fu Zhi Guo in Chinese, literally a place richly endowed with natural resources. Chengdu, as the capital, is extremely productive. The Min and Tuo Rivers, two branches of the Yangtze River, connected to 40 other rivers, supply an irrigation area of more than 700 square kilometres (270.27 square miles) with 150-180 million kilowatts of water. title: b'IIR 2022'
description: b'Italian Information Retrieval Workshop'
Call For Papers: b'\nScope\rThe purpose of the Italian Information Retrieval Workshop (IIR) is to provide a meeting forum for stimulating and disseminating research in Information Retrieval, where Italian researchers (especially young ones) and researchers affiliated with Italian institutions can network and discuss their research results in an informal way.\r IIR 2022 is the 12th edition of the Italian Information Retrieval Workshop. It will take place on June 29th - July 1st, 2022 and it is jointly organised by Politecnico di Milano (where it will take place on both June 29th and July 1st) and by the University of Milano Bicocca (where it will take place on June the 30th).\r IIR 2022 aims to be an in-presence event. Nevertheless, on-line presentations and participation is allowed.\r Participation to the IIR 2022 workshop will be free of charge. However, advance registration will be strictly required.\r Topics\rIIR 2022 offers an opportunity to present and discuss both theoretical and empirical research. Relevant topics include, but are not restricted to:\r Search and Ranking. Research on core IR algorithmic topics, including IR at scale, covering topics such as:\rQueries and query analysis\rWeb search, including link analysis, sponsored search, search advertising, adversarial search and spam, and vertical search\rRetrieval models and ranking, including diversity and aggregated search\rEfficiency and scalability\rTheoretical models and foundations of information retrieval and access\rFuture Directions. Research with theoretical or empirical contributions on new technical or social aspects of IR, especially in more speculative directions or with emerging technologies, covering topics such as:\rNovel approaches to IR\rEthics, economics, and politics\rApplications of search to social good\rIR with new devices, including wearable computing, neuroinformatics, sensors, Internet-of-Things, vehicles\rDomain-Specific Applications. Research focusing on domain-specific IR challenges, covering topics such as:\rSocial search\rSearch in structured data including email search and entity search\rMultimedia search\rEducation\rLegal\rHealth, including genomics and bioinformatics\rAcademic search\rOther domains such as digital libraries, enterprise, news search, app search, archival search\rContent Analysis, Recommendation and Classification. Research focusing on recommender systems, rich content representations and content analysis, covering topics such as:\rFiltering and recommender systems\rDocument representation\rContent analysis and information extraction, including summarization, text representation, readability, sentiment analysis, and opinion mining\rCross- and multilingual search\rClustering, classification, and topic models\rArtificial Intelligence, Semantics, and Dialog. Research bridging AI and IR, especially toward deep semantics and dialog with intelligent agents, covering topics such as:\rQuestion answering\rConversational systems and retrieval, including spoken language interfaces, dialog management systems, and intelligent chat systems\rSemantics and knowledge graphs\rDeep learning for IR, embeddings, and agents\rHuman Factors and Interfaces. Research into user-centric aspects of IR, including user interfaces, behavior modeling, privacy, and interactive systems, covering topics such as:\rMining and modeling search activity, including user and task models, click models, log analysis, behavioral analysis, and attention modeling\rInteractive and personalized search\rCollaborative search, social tagging and crowdsourcing\rInformation privacy and security\rEvaluation. Research that focuses on the measurement and evaluation of IR systems, covering topics such as:\rUser-centered evaluation methods, including measures of user experience and performance, user engagement and search task design\rTest collections and evaluation metrics, including the development of new test collections\rEye-tracking and physiological approaches, such as fMRI\rEvaluation of novel information access tasks and systems such as multi-turn information access\rStatistical methods and reproducibility issues in information retrieval evaluation\rSubmissions\rSubmissions of full research papers must be in English, in PDF format in the CEUR-WS single-column conference format available at http://ceur-ws.org/Vol-XXX/CEURART.zip.\r Submission will be peer reviewed and accepted papers will appear in the CEUR workshop series (at authors\xe2\x80\x99 discretion). Papers may range from theoretical works to system descriptions. We particularly encourage PhD students or Early-Stage Researchers to submit their research. We also welcome contributions from the industry and papers describing ongoing funded projects which may result useful to the IIR community.\rThe conference language is English.\r Authors are invited to submit one of the following types of contributions:\r Full original papers (10 pages, plus additional pages for references if needed)\rShort original papers (5 pages, plus additional pages for references if needed)\rExtended abstracts containing descriptions of ongoing projects or presenting already published results (up to 4 pages, plus additional pages for references if needed). If presenting already published results the extended abstract should be single blind and contain a reference to the original published paper.\rSubmission will be through Easychair at https://easychair.org/conferences/?conf=iir2022.\n\t'

description: b'7th Edition of International Conference on Dentistry and Oral Health (American Dental 2023).'
Call For Papers: b"\nAfter the highly fruitful four editions of dentistry and oral health conference, Magnus Group is delighted to invite you to its preeminent event \xe2\x80\x9c7th Edition of International Conference on Dentistry and Oral Health.\xe2\x80\x9d (American Dental 2023).\rDue to the pandemic and restrictions imposed, this year the worldwide summit will be held in a hybrid format with both virtual and in-person versions at Orlando, USA during April 17-19, 2023.\rHealthcare professionals, Dentists, Dental hygienists, academicians, oral care experts, scientists and researchers will share plethora of knowledge covering all essential sessions of dentistry focused on its unique theme \xe2\x80\x9cBlending Today's Lifestyle with Dental Trends for Vibrant Smiles.\xe2\x80\x9d Through effective communication, community development, training, and multidisciplinary gatherings, the conferences help to support the generation and dissemination of oral disease knowledge, treatment and therapeutic approaches across the globe. The international conference on dentistry and oral health provides a forum for the exchange of advanced and significant research findings in the field of dentistry and oral health. 3rd International Conference on IoT, Blockchain & Cloud Computing (IBCOM 2022)

November 26 ~ 27, 2022, London, United Kingdom

Scope & Topics

3rd International Conference on IoT, Blockchain & Cloud Computing (IBCOM 2022)will provide an excellent international forum for sharing knowledge and results in theory, methodology and applications of IoT, Blockchain and Cloud Computing.

Authors are solicited to contribute to the conference by submitting articles that illustrate research results, projects, surveying works and industrial experiences that describe significant advances in the following areas, but are not limited to.

  • Block Chain issues and trends\r

  • IoT Experimental Results and Deployment Scenarios\r
  • IoT Applications and Services\r
  • IoT Security and Privacy\r
  • IoT enabled Innovation and Entrepreneurship\r
  • Applications based on IoT and Cloud\r
  • Case Studies and Theories in Cloud Computing\r
  • Cloud as a Service\r
  • Cloud Infrastructure\r
  • Cloud Management\r
  • Cloud Security\r
  • Cloud Applications\r
  • Cloud Computing Technologies\r
  • Big data in Cloud\r
  • Cloud Computing Architecture\r
  • Cloud Computing based IoT technologies\r
  • Cloud storage for IoT\r
  • Connectivity and Networking\r
  • Data storage and management in Cloud computing\r
  • Energy management and programming environments\r
  • Experimental Results and Deployment Scenarios\r
  • Security and privacy in Clouds and IoT\r
  • Security techniques for the Cloud\r
  • The Open Cloud: Cloud Computing and open source

Paper Submission

Authors are invited to submit papers through the conference Submission System by August 27, 2022. Submissions must be original and should not have been published previously or be under consideration for publication while being evaluated for this conference. The proceedings of the conference will be published by Computer Science Conference Proceedings in Computer Science & Information Technology (CS & IT) series (Confirmed).

Selected papers from IBCOM 2022, after further revisions, will be published in the special issues of the following journals.

  • International Journal of Ubiquitous Computing (IJU)

International Conference on Software Engineering and Automation (SEAU 2022)

November 12 ~ 13, 2022, Chennai, India

Scope & Topics

International Conference on Software Engineering and Automation (SEAU 2022) will provide an excellent international forum for sharing knowledge and results in theory, methodology and applications of Software Engineering and Automation. The goal of this Conference is to bring together researchers and practitioners from academia and industry to focus on understanding Modern software engineering concepts and establishing new collaborations in these areas.

Authors are solicited to contribute to the Conference by submitting articles that illustrate research results, projects, surveying works and industrial experiences that describe significant advances in the areas of software engineering & applications.

Topics of interest include, but are not limited to, the following

  • Advanced Topics in Software Engineering
  • Agile and Lean Software Development
  • IoT software engineering
  • Knowledge-based Systems and Formal Methods
  • Languages and Formal Methods
  • Managing Software Projects
  • Multimedia and Visual Software Engineering
  • Open Source Software
  • Quality Management
  • Service-oriented Software Engineering (SOSE)
  • Software Engineering Decision Making
  • Software Engineering for Big Data
  • Software Engineering for Machine Learning
  • Software Engineering Practice
  • Software Maintenance and Testing
  • Software Performance
  • Software Process
  • Software Security
  • Web Engineering
  • Web-based Education Systems and Learning Applications
  • Automated usability and user experience testing
  • Automation and control systems
  • Formal methods and theories for testing and test automation
  • Natural Language Processing (NLP) Based Test Automation
  • Network Automation
  • Computer Vision & Automation
  • Robotics, Automation and Signal Processing
  • Security Automation
  • Software Test Automation
  • Test automation of large, complex system

Paper Submission

Authors are invited to submit papers through the conference Submission System by August 27, 2022. Submissions must be original and should not have been published previously or be under consideration for publication while being evaluated for this conference. The proceedings of the conference will be published by Computer Science Conference Proceedings in Computer Science & Information Technology (CS & IT) series (Confirmed).

Selected papers from SEAU 2022, after further revisions, will be published in the special issue of the following journals.

  • International Journal of Software Engineering & Applications (IJSEA) - ERA Indexed
  • International Journal of Computer-Aided technologies (IJCAx)
  • Advanced Computing: An International Journal (ACIJ)
  • International Journal of Computer Science, Engineering and Information Technology (IJCSEIT)
  • International Journal in Foundations of Computer Science & Technology (IJFCST)
  • International Journal of Information Technology, Control and Automation (IJITCA)

Important Dates

Submission Deadline: August 27, 2022
Authors Notification: September 25, 2022
Final Manuscript Due: October 04, 2022
'

Call For Papers: b'\nEAI AFRICOMM 2022 will be held as an on-site conference and if needed, Accepted Authors who are unable to attend the event in person will be given an option to present remotely.\r SCOPE\rDeveloping countries are embracing the use of ICT in order to improve performance of both the public and private sectors. A great challenges is, however, resource availability. Researchers and practitioners alike, from both the global north and south have developed interest on developing the means and ways of efficient diffusion of ICT in the resource constrained environment. AFRICOMM 2022 aims to bring together researchers, practitioners, and policy makers in ICT to discuss issues and trends, recent research, innovation advances and on-the-field experiences related to title: b'EAI HealthyIoT 2022'
description: b'EAI HealthyIoT 2022 - 9th EAI International Conference on IoT Technologies for HealthCare'
Categories: b'e-health'
Call For Papers: b'\nEAI HealthyIoT 2022 will be held as an on-site conference and if needed, Accepted Authors who are unable to attend the event in person will be given an option to present remotely.\r SCOPE\rHealthyIoT 2022 is the ninth edition of an international scientific event series dedicated to the Internet of Things and Healthcare. Traditionally, this conference covers multiple aspects of using IoT in healthcare and brings together technology experts, researchers, industry and international authorities contributing towards the design, development, and deployment of healthcare solutions based on IoT technologies, standards, and procedures. title: b'EAI SmartGov 2022'
description: b'EAI SmartGov 2022 - 4th EAI International Conference on Smart Governance for Sustainable Smart Cities'
Categories: b'smart cities'
Call For Papers: b'\nEAI SmartGov 2022 will be held as an on-site conference and if needed, Accepted Authors who are unable to attend the event in person will be given an option to present remotely.\r SCOPE\r The emerging research and development for smart of everything towards fast, reliable and sustainable services make every government think for the implementation of the latest technologies in its services so that citizens demand in this rapidly urbanized society can be fulfilled. Software-Defined Networking and Network Function Virtualization, 5th Generation and beyond mobile communication technologies, Industry/Society 5.0 and beyond are the major emerging paradigms as well as drivers of change to build smart and sustainable society. Every government has to adapt their policies to address the technological changes and effectively implement policies towards smart service provisioning. Smart city believes in the smartness of everything that are directly related to smart service provisioning to citizens from the local level of government to the central government, which understands the dynamics of changes in the people\xe2\x80\x99s living standards and acts and adapts as a smart government. This means that smart cities need to find new ways to interact with businesses, thought-leaders, suppliers, residents, and visitors. Greater transparency and frequent, two-way communication are expected with the co-creation of public services allowing for greater innovation. Advances in data science allow relevant, real-time data to be transformed into useful information to understand urban behavior and infrastructure needs. This can support evidence-based decision-making, automated responses and autonomously managed procedures. Realizing this potential, however, raises concerns about privacy and security issues, the resilience of critical information infrastructures, and the unintended consequences as social expectations and behaviors are shaped by algorithms. In this regard, it is crucial for smart cities to provide trustworthy services which are secure, privacy-aware and sustainable. Our aim is to promote the development of secure and sustainable smart cities with smart governance.\r ***\rGeneral Chair\rDanda B Rawat\rHoward University\r Technical Program Committee Chairs\rKayhan Zrar Ghafoor\rSalahaddin University-Erbil\r Babu R. Dawadi\rInstitute of Engineerring, Tribhuvan University\r General Co-Chair\rSubarna Shakya\rInstitute of Engineerring, Tribhuvan University\r ***\r PUBLICATIONS\r All registered papers will be submitted for publishing by Springer and made available through SpringerLink Digital Library.\r Proceedings will be submitted for inclusion in leading indexing services, such as Web of Science, Compendex, Scopus, DBLP, EU Digital Library, IO-Port, MatchSciNet, Inspec and Zentralblatt MATH.\r Authors of selected best accepted and presented papers will be invited to submit an extended version to\r Mobile Networks and Applications (MONET) Journal (IF: 3.426)\rWireless Networks (WINET) Journal (IF:2.602)\rAdditional publication opportunities:\r EAI Transactions series (Open Access)\rEAI/Springer Innovations in Communications and Computing Book Series\r(titles in this series are indexed in Ei Compendex, Web of Science & Scopus)\r ***\r TOPICS\rThe SmartGov 2022 will serve as a forum for researchers from academia, government and industries, to exchange ideas, present new results, and provide future visions on these topics. TOPICS INCLUDE:\r - Smart City/Governance foundations, models, frameworks, and principles for smart cities\r- Smart policies for smart governance\r- Intelligent and programmable networking for smart cities\r- Cybersecurity and privacy for smart cities\r- Cloud/fog/edge/mist computing for smart cities\r- IoT and Cyber Physical Systems for smart cities,\r- Secure and Trustworthy Computing for smart cities\r- Social media and urban awareness\r- Blockchain for smart governance and smart cities\r- Data and evidence-based policymaking\r- Urban big data from heterogeneous sources\r- AI and Machine Learning for secure and sustainable smart cities\r- Smart governance practices, dynamics, challenges and trade-offs\r- Alignment of smart city policies with social and environmental sustainability goals\r- Governance of transformation processes\r- Measurement and monitoring of smart governance process and outcomes\r- Smart governance-related case-studies and experience reports\r- Citizen-centricity and citizen-driven solutions for smart cities\r- Co-production and collaborative forms of service design and delivery\r- Open governance, participatory decision making and accountability\r- Urban innovation, new business models, legal and normative frameworks\r- Broadband communications for smart cities and rural communities\r- Case studies for smart city implementation in developing nations\r- Impact of emerging technologies (e.g., AI, machine learning, federated learning, blockchain, sensor networks, intelligent transportation systems) for smart governance.\r ***\rThis event is organized by EAI (www.eai.eu).\r EAI \xe2\x80\x93 European Alliance for Innovation is a non-profit organization and a professional community established in cooperation with the European Commission to empower global research and innovation, and to promote cooperation between European and International ICT communities.\n\t'

title: b'CAD 10.2 2022'
description: b'Culture and Dialogue 10.2: Cross-Cultural Encounters'
Categories: b'philosophy' b'humanities' b'hermeneutics'
Call For Papers: b'\nCulture and Dialogue\r An international peer reviewed print and electronic journal \rof cross-cultural philosophy and humanities\r www.brill.com/cad\rISSN 2222-3282\r Honorary Member: Tzvetan Todorov 1939-2017\rEditor in Chief: Gerald Cipriani National University of Ireland, Galway UNESCO, D.S. Likhachev Russian Research Institute of Cultural and Natural Heritage, Moscow\rEditor:\tMartin Ovens\t                University of Oxford (UK)\rAssociate Editor:Loni Reynolds\t        University of Roehampton (UK)\rManuscript Editor: Kaitlin Sager\tTulane University (USA)\rBook Review Editor: Robert Clarke\tLancaster University (UK)\r Culture and Dialogue provides a forum for researchers from philosophy as well as other disciplines who study cultural formations dialogically, through comparative analysis, or within the tradition of hermeneutics. The journal publishes one volume of two issues each year. The first issue welcomes manuscripts that consider the arts and cultures of the dialogue, namely the broad theme of \xe2\x80\x9cCulture and Dialogue\xe2\x80\x9d in all its forms, from all perspectives, and through all methods. The second issue seeks to bring manuscripts together with a common denominator such as \xe2\x80\x9cPhilosophy and the Dialogue,\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cArt in Conversation,\xe2\x80\x9d \xe2\x80\x9cComparing Cultures,\xe2\x80\x9d or \xe2\x80\x9cDialogical Ethics.\xe2\x80\x9d \r 2022 marks the twentieth anniversary of the passing away of Hans-Georg Gadamer (1900-2002).  What a better opportunity to reflect on the nature of cross-cultural dialogue in all its forms? Volume 10.2 of Culture and Dialogue will focus on the theme of \r Cross-Cultural Encounters\r We welcome contributions from any areas of cross-cultural humanities and the arts that explore in one way or another one of the following topics:\r \xe2\x80\xa2 Dialogical encounters: theories and practices\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Cultures of sameness and otherness from a variety of perspectives (Eastern, African, Western, Indian etc.) \r\xe2\x80\xa2 Reflections on cross-cultural formations within a particular field (philosophical, artistic, anthropological, social, religious, political, psychological, scientific etc.)\r\xe2\x80\xa2 Critique of the idea of cross-cultural thought from within the traditions of interpretive or analytic philosophies\r  Submissions to: irgcd@mail.com\rNotes for Authors:\thttps://brill.com/fileasset/downloads_products/Author_Instructions/CAD.pdf\rDeadline: 1st July 2022 \r  International Research Group for Culture and Dialogue\rirgcd.wordpress.com\rCulture and Dialogue is endorsed by the UNESCO Chair in Comparative Studies of Spiritual Traditions, Their Specific Cultures and Interreligious Dialogue (St. Petersburg/Moscow)\r\n'

Call For Papers: b"\n CONFERENCE TOPICS\r We are looking forward to proposals related to the following topics (and many more!):\r Back-end\r Cloud\r Software Architecture\r Cybersecurity\r Microservices\r Performance\r Devops\r Kubernetes\r Docker\r CI/CD\r Testing\r Front-end\r Micro-frontend\r Design/UX\r Accessibility\r API\r AI/ML\r Data\r Web 3.0\r Quantum\r Deep Learning\r AR/VR/XR\r Diversity in Tech\r IT Careers\r Team Growth\r Ethics\r Green Tech\r This list of topics is only indicative, in the application there are many more categories. In any case submissions that do not fit into any of these categories are also welcome, provided that they are relevant or inspirational for the tech community.\r SESSIONS\r You can submit your proposal for 2 different kind of sessions:\r - tech talk 45 minutes (Q&A included): it's a standard talk where you can introduce a technology for example.\r - tech talk 15', also called lightining talk: it's a very short presentation lasting only a few minutes, that must be very focused on a specific feature of a technology or a very quick use case\r For all sessions, speakers are required to be present at the venue, it is not possible to pre-register or hold an online session.\r LANGUAGE\r Sessions can be held in English or Italian. The language in which you prefer to hold the talk is requested in the submission.\r SUBMISSION STRUCTURE\r Topics\rWe appreciate novelty and real case studies: take into account what could be useful to our audience, according to your experience. Also, if you are planning to present a talk you have already delivered elsewhere, try to add a twist, a fresh touch.\rThe audience of our tech conference is getting more and more international and skilled every year: our main aim is to offer them a real opportunity of growth in a multicultural oriented environment.\r Talk title\rThe title of your talk is probably the hardest part of your application: it has to capture the attendees\xe2\x80\x99 attention and spark their interest. Keep it short, memorable, compelling, with a touch of personality, hinting at the subject and focus of your talk.\r Abstract\rPlease note that the abstract field can contain a maximum number of characters (spaces included), so if you exceed this limit it will be cut from the system.\r Levels\r     Beginner: Introductory talk on a cutting edge technology/framework/language etc. Keep always in mind, even when you are delivering a beginner session, that your audience is going to be made up of IT, experienced professionals: so avoid presenting the very basics of your topic.\r    Intermediate: A detailed analysis on some aspects of well-known technologies, issues, topics.\r    Advanced: A deep dive talk for a keen and skillful audience. This is the talk you\xe2\x80\x99d wish to attend to learn something new on your key topic.\r    Non-technical: A wide-ranging and far-reaching proposal on cross-cutting themes: personal career experience and points of view will be highly appreciated.\r First-time speaker?\rIf you are not sure how to craft the perfect application or how to deliver a session that rocks, feel free to contact us: our Program Committee will be happy to review your proposal and provide feedback.\r SELECTION PROCESS\r The proposals are collected through a public Call for Papers and they are evaluated separately by both tech communities and our Program Committee.\rThe agenda is created by the Program Committee, on the basis of the outcome of the voting process and the topics chosen for the conference.\r What do our attendees look for?\r Our conference attracts developers, IT professionals and tech lovers with diverse professional backgrounds. We are looking for talks which provide them with:\r     Showcase of technical excellence, latest research and cutting-edge technologies\r    Hands-on knowledge that could be useful for their job\r    Best practices and case studies that can help them become better developers\r    Code! Remember to show some lines of code and some demos\r    Inspirational talks and visions on how technology is shaping the future\r    Talks with great contents, which do not hold a hidden marketing pitch\r YOUR SPEAKER PROFILE\r Please, remember to keep updated your profile with the current job title and a high quality picture. This will help us to do a better promotion of your talk \xf0\x9f\x99\x82\r Guidelines for a good quality picture:\r     QUALITY: high quality and colour image; real photos, no caricatures\r    DESCRIPTION: intact half-length figure (i.e. no cut parts, face clearly visible, no external objects)\r    DIMENSION: minimum size 600px short side\r    BACKGROUND: neutral or uniform\r \n"

Call For Papers: b'\nCFP  \rAPA Central, Gatherings 2023  \r2/22/23 to 2/25/23 \r Denver, Colorado \r A session organized by the Institute for Studies in Pragmaticism \r  philosophia naturalis  \r Making Sense of Relations and Realities  \r  The various recent approaches to quantum worlds appear to be reaching a consensus: that spacetime is quantized, relational, and emergent out of a fundamentally new, pre-geometric order that exists \xe2\x80\x9cbefore\xe2\x80\x9d and \xe2\x80\x9cbelow.\xe2\x80\x9d Conventional reality, then, emerges as an explicate order from more fundamental, relational pre-geometric and pre-quantum implicate order(s), which exist beyond conventional science and philosophy.   \rThis pre-geometric implicate order has the potential to answer the two most fundamental questions in all of the philosophia naturalis: what is the origin of spacetime and the fields within it, and ultimately, why is there something rather than nothing? Hence, the sub-Planckian order promises profound consequences, not just for foundational (meta)physics, but also for cosmic evolution in quantum cosmology and human knowledge of it.    \rMany scholars have explored these ideas, most notably the physicists David Bohm and Carlo Rovelli, and within the tradition of relational and process philosophy (Peirce, Bergson, Whitehead, Derrida, Deleuze, Guattari, DeLanda, et al.).  \rThe session invites papers to discuss historical and current positions towards a genuinely holistic philosophia naturalis, which unites philosophy and science beyond the traditional rational-empirical academic disciplinary boundaries.   \r Please send your abstract (300-500 words) to Elize Bisanz \xe2\x80\x93 elize.bisanz@ttu.edu\xe2\x80\x94 by July 30th, 2022. \r\n'
